{"type":null,"faqId":23347,"title":"How can I reduce mobile data usage?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n.s2{font-weight:bold;}\n.p1{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n <span>Connect to a Wi-Fi network if there is one available.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>Turn off the mobile data connection when you are not using mobile data.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>When browsing web pages, you can prevent images from loading on the page if you do not need to view them.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>In the </span><span class=\"s2\">Browser</span><span> interface, open the options menu, select </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings &gt; Bandwidth management</span><span> and deselect </span><span class=\"s2\">Load images</span><span>.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>Disable background data syncing if not needed.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Swipe downwards from the status bar to display shortcut switches and then touch </span><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=78506\" style=\"width:0.30555555in;height:0.22361112in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><span> to turn off the auto sync function.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>Close the apps that you are not using.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Open the list of recently-used apps and close the apps that you are no longer using.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n <span>Stop apps in the background from accessing the Internet via mobile data.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Go to </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings</span><span> and select </span><span class=\"s2\">Networked apps</span><span>. Then select the apps for which you want to restrict Internet access and turn off the corresponding mobile data switch.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"7347","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1429846210000,"seriesProductName":"G6-L11,G760-L01,Jazz-L11,S10-231L,S10-231u,S7-721u,Sophia-L10,Y220-U10,Y221-U22,Y330-U01,Y330-U11,Y330-U11,Y511-U10,Y520-U22,Y550-L01","visitedTimes":6,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"mobile data usage; data usage","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}